      Possible browser values are: CHROME, FIREFOX, IEXPLORER

      For example: if you want all the tests to run on "Chrome", set the browser parameter to CHROME.

      Parameters:
      browser - the browser that the tests will run

    • capturePage

      public static java.lang.String capturePage​(java.lang.String folderName, java.lang.String subFolderName, java.lang.String imageMainName, java.lang.String imageAditionalName)
      Captures a screenshot of the current visible page.

      The screenshots will be saved in a folder/sub-folder, that will be created inside the test results directory.

      The path/link to the saved image will be added to the tests results Report Log

      Parameters:
      folderName - the folder name where the sub-folder and image will be saved
      subFolderName - the sub-folder name where the image will be saved
      imageMainName - the desired name for the image
      imageAditionalName - the additional name that can be added to the image main name (optional - can be null)
      Returns:
      link the link to the screenshot

    • assertTextPresent

      public void assertTextPresent​(java.lang.String... strings)
      Assert if each "text" (string) passed through the parameter is Present on the page.

      You can pass as many strings as you like, separated by comma. The test will fail if at least one element isn't found on the Page.

      E.g.: assertTextPresent("String 1", "String 2", "String 3");

      Parameters:
      strings - the texts that will be validated
      Throws:
      java.lang.AssertionError - if at least one string isn't found

    • assertElementPresentByName

      public void assertElementPresentByName​(java.lang.String... strings) throws java.lang.AssertionError
      Validates if an element, searched by tag name, is present on the page.

      You can pass as many strings as you like, separated by comma. The test will fail if at least one element isn't found on the page.

      E.g.: isElementPresentByName("name1", "name2", "name3");

      OBS.: Selenium does not validate HTML tags inside frame. For example, if the page that will be validated with this method has a tag "name" inside a frame, the test will fail.

      Parameters:
      strings - the tag names that you want validate
      Throws:
      java.lang.AssertionError - if at least one tag name isn't found

      Validates if the given option stringValue is selected in the element selectName.

      If the value passed by parameter is not the same as on the page, the test will fail.

      E.g.: optionIsSelected("SelectTagName", "optionValue);

      Parameters:
      selectName - the name of the selector
      stringValue - the value that should be selected
      Throws:
      java.lang.AssertionError - if the current selected option is different from stringValue

    • assertListsAreEqual

      public void assertListsAreEqual​(java.util.List<org.openqa.selenium.WebElement> dropdownOptions, java.lang.String[] listOptionsExpected, boolean compareOrder, boolean caseSensitive) throws java.lang.AssertionError
      Compares the options inside a dropdown (List<WebElement>) in the page with the options inside an expected given list.

      If the options are different, the assert will fail.

      E.g.: compareListOption(webElement, arrayOptions, true, true);

      Parameters:
      dropdownOptions - dropdown (List<WebElement>) in the page
      listOptionsExpected - list with the expected options, that will be compared to the options in the dropdown
      compareOrder - indicates if the order has to be considered or not
      caseSensitive - indicates if the comparison has to be case sensitive or not
      Throws:
      java.lang.AssertionError - if the dropdown is different from the expected list
